---
name: "Svelte guidelines (renderer)"
description: "Keep views thin; use feature stores/services for logic; avoid Node APIs in views."
globs: ["app/renderer/src/**/*.svelte"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Views should be mostly declarative; defer state and IO to feature `store.ts` / `service.ts`.
- Use Svelte stores for shared state; derive when possible.
- Prefer explicit subscribe/unsubscribe for stores in this codebase.
- Never import Node/Electron modules in views; use preload-exposed APIs.

